WEBVTT

1
00:00:45.160 --> 00:00:48.760
FEMALE NARRATOR:
<i>Some people say that fairies</i>
<i>are the stuff of fantasy.</i>

2
00:00:49.240 --> 00:00:54.240
<i>They think the world is just</i>
<i>what you can touch</i>
<i>and hear and see,</i>

3
00:00:54.360 --> 00:00:58.040
<i>while others say</i>
<i>the tales and legends</i>
<i>cannot be dismissed.</i>

4
00:00:58.680 --> 00:01:03.360
<i>They believe with</i>
<i>all their hearts</i>
<i>that fairies truly do exist.</i>

5
00:01:05.280 --> 00:01:09.680
<i>Throughout all time,</i>
<i>human beings and</i>
<i>fairies never met,</i>

6
00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:16.040
<i>till one very</i>
<i>special summer that</i>
<i>we shall not soon forget.</i>

7
00:01:21.920 --> 00:01:23.120
<i>(SUMMER'S JUST BEGUN</i> PLAYING)

8
00:01:27.440 --> 00:01:30.720
<i>WOMAN: ♪ Life is rising up</i>

9
00:01:30.800 --> 00:01:33.480
<i>♪ Surging forth</i>
<i>in all directions</i>

10
00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:39.440
<i>♪ Every little buttercup</i>
<i>Is reaching out</i>
<i>to find connections</i>

11
00:01:39.480 --> 00:01:42.600
<i>♪ Every blade of grass</i>
<i>Will touch the sunlight</i>

12
00:01:43.200 --> 00:01:46.120
<i>♪ The rain will</i>
<i>touch the ground</i>

13
00:01:46.160 --> 00:01:51.000
<i>♪ Growing greener</i>
<i>than it was before</i>

14
00:01:52.880 --> 00:01:58.640
<i>♪ Bees are droning by</i>
<i>Spider silk is</i>
<i>softly spinning</i>

15
00:01:58.760 --> 00:02:04.480
<i>♪ Not a cloud in the sky</i>
<i>You know it's only</i>
<i>the beginning</i>

16
00:02:04.720 --> 00:02:11.280
<i>♪ Every little blossom,</i>
<i>every flower</i>
<i>Flings its petals wide</i>

17
00:02:11.360 --> 00:02:16.000
<i>♪ As the season</i>
<i>comes round</i>
<i>Once more</i>

18
00:02:16.080 --> 00:02:17.320
(BOTH LAUGHING)

19
00:02:17.360 --> 00:02:20.160
Hey, Tink!
You ready for your first
summer on the mainland?

20
00:02:20.280 --> 00:02:23.400
Absolutely!
It's so beautiful out here.

21
00:02:23.520 --> 00:02:25.960
I can't believe
we get to stay
for the whole season.

22
00:02:26.480 --> 00:02:29.400
Well,
what are we waiting for?
Race you down!

23
00:02:30.520 --> 00:02:33.640
<i>♪ The breeze is blowing</i>
<i>light and sweet</i>

24
00:02:33.680 --> 00:02:36.880
<i>♪ The grass,</i>
<i>a carpet at your feet</i>

25
00:02:36.960 --> 00:02:41.200
<i>♪ Catch the colors</i>
<i>Feel the heat of the sun</i>

26
00:02:43.360 --> 00:02:46.400
<i>♪ All the sparrows</i>
<i>in the dell</i>

27
00:02:46.480 --> 00:02:49.520
<i>♪ Swirling round</i>
<i>like a carousel</i>

28
00:02:49.720 --> 00:02:53.520
<i>♪ Singing loud enough</i>
<i>to tell everyone</i>

29
00:02:53.560 --> 00:02:54.600
Hi, guys.

30
00:02:54.680 --> 00:02:56.400
<i>♪ Summer's just begun</i>

31
00:03:00.680 --> 00:03:02.560
<i>♪ Summer's just begun</i>

32
00:03:05.760 --> 00:03:08.400
There it is, Tink.
Fairy camp!

33
00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:11.440
<i>♪ All the winters,</i>
<i>all the springs</i>

34
00:03:11.720 --> 00:03:14.640
<i>♪ Lead us here</i>
<i>on fairy wings</i>

35
00:03:14.720 --> 00:03:18.920
<i>♪ A season of</i>
<i>a thousand things</i>
<i>To be done</i>

36
00:03:19.480 --> 00:03:21.240
<i>♪ Summer's just begun</i>

37
00:03:25.920 --> 00:03:27.880
<i>♪ Summer's just begun</i>

38
00:03:30.920 --> 00:03:32.240
Hiya, Cheese!

39
00:03:32.280 --> 00:03:33.640
<i>♪ Summer's just begun ♪</i>

40
00:03:33.720 --> 00:03:34.840
Did you have a nice flight?

41
00:03:34.920 --> 00:03:36.440
BOBBLE: Incoming!

42
00:03:36.480 --> 00:03:38.040
BOBBLE: Keep her level!
Keep her level!

43
00:03:38.080 --> 00:03:39.920
CLANK: Gear it down, Bobble!

44
00:03:40.040 --> 00:03:41.520
(EXCLAIMING) Oh-ho!

45
00:03:41.600 --> 00:03:43.080
Smashing landing,
Clanky.

46
00:03:43.200 --> 00:03:44.480
Thank you, Bobble.

47
00:03:44.560 --> 00:03:47.360
Guys, I think you may
have over-packed.

48
00:03:47.640 --> 00:03:49.240
Come on, Tink.
Let's go inside.

49
00:03:49.280 --> 00:03:50.440
Inside?

50
00:03:51.040 --> 00:03:53.920
Tink, fairy camp
isn't out here
in the open.

51
00:03:54.080 --> 00:03:55.960
We need to stay hidden
from the humans.

52
00:03:56.040 --> 00:03:58.000
We do?
Uh. Yeah.

53
00:03:58.280 --> 00:04:00.640
That's why fairy
camp is in here.

54
00:04:08.720 --> 00:04:13.280
MALE FAIRY:
Cicadas, one at a time.
You, you and you. You, too.

55
00:04:14.320 --> 00:04:18.440
Wow. It's like
all of Pixie Hollow
under one tree!

56
00:04:20.320 --> 00:04:21.880
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

57
00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:32.960
Blaze!

58
00:04:33.440 --> 00:04:34.480
Hmm?

59
00:04:34.960 --> 00:04:36.160
(CHATTERS HAPPILY)

60
00:04:40.200 --> 00:04:41.320
(LAUGHING)

61
00:04:41.400 --> 00:04:42.480
(GASPS)

62
00:04:53.560 --> 00:04:56.160
(MUSICAL CHIRPING)

63
00:04:57.600 --> 00:04:58.840
(OFF TUNE CHIRP)

64
00:04:59.160 --> 00:05:00.840
(LAUGHING)

65
00:05:01.840 --> 00:05:04.840
TINKER BELL: Wow!
The Queen Anne's lace
is looking beautiful.

66
00:05:04.920 --> 00:05:06.000
How are
the looms working?

67
00:05:06.080 --> 00:05:08.080
Fine, thanks to you, Tink.

68
00:05:08.160 --> 00:05:12.960
Next. Next. Next.

69
00:05:13.040 --> 00:05:14.200
How's the bee-liner working?

70
00:05:14.240 --> 00:05:16.560
Like a dream, Tink.
Thanks.

71
00:05:16.640 --> 00:05:19.040
Great. Need any
help with that wagon?

72
00:05:19.080 --> 00:05:20.560
MALE GARDEN FAIRY:
No, thanks.
She's running fine.

73
00:05:20.640 --> 00:05:22.520
Okay. Glad to hear it.

74
00:05:22.720 --> 00:05:23.840
(GRUNTING)

75
00:05:23.880 --> 00:05:25.960
Here's the first
week's supply.

76
00:05:26.040 --> 00:05:27.840
Okay, I'm off.

77
00:05:27.880 --> 00:05:30.280
I gotta go deliver
pixie dust to the other
fairy camps,

78
00:05:30.360 --> 00:05:32.800
but I'll see you
in a couple days.

79
00:05:33.040 --> 00:05:36.720
Oh, and Tink! Don't worry.
You'll find something to fix.

80
00:05:38.720 --> 00:05:40.040
I hope so.

81
00:05:40.240 --> 00:05:42.800
In the meantime,
I need to go find
some lost things.

82
00:05:42.880 --> 00:05:45.000
Hold on,
little miss spare parts.

83
00:05:45.080 --> 00:05:47.720
You're not going near
the human house, are you?

84
00:05:47.760 --> 00:05:49.400
(GASPS) There's
a human house?

85
00:05:49.440 --> 00:05:52.320
No! I mean, yes, but no.

86
00:05:52.400 --> 00:05:53.760
We stay away from humans.

87
00:05:53.800 --> 00:05:55.160
Oh, Iridessa!

88
00:05:55.560 --> 00:05:56.560
(BLOWING KISS)

89
00:05:56.640 --> 00:05:59.760
Tinker Bell knows that,
don't you?

90
00:05:59.800 --> 00:06:02.120
Define "stay away."

91
00:06:02.280 --> 00:06:04.880
(GROANS) It's gonna be
a long summer.

92
00:06:04.960 --> 00:06:06.080
Grouchy.

93
00:06:06.360 --> 00:06:08.560
Oh, that's just
Vidia being Vidia.

94
00:06:08.600 --> 00:06:10.520
No, the air.
It smells...

95
00:06:10.640 --> 00:06:12.120
(SNIFFING) ...grouchy.

96
00:06:12.760 --> 00:06:14.160
We might be in
for a storm.

97
00:06:14.240 --> 00:06:15.640
Come on, Sil.

98
00:06:15.880 --> 00:06:18.280
The sun is shining,
the air is warm.

99
00:06:18.360 --> 00:06:20.800
It's a beautiful day.
Nothing's gonna...

100
00:06:22.640 --> 00:06:23.840
(GASPING)

101
00:06:24.120 --> 00:06:25.440
(CAR ENGINE RATTLING)

102
00:06:27.960 --> 00:06:29.120
(BLOWING HORN)

103
00:06:46.040 --> 00:06:47.280
(CAR APPROACHING)

104
00:06:52.320 --> 00:06:53.400
(GASPING)

105
00:07:09.400 --> 00:07:11.360
(GASPS) Tinker Bell.

106
00:07:22.600 --> 00:07:23.680
(LIZZY LAUGHING)

107
00:07:23.760 --> 00:07:25.840
Thank goodness
we're here, Father.

108
00:07:25.920 --> 00:07:27.600
It's just like
I remember it.

109
00:07:27.680 --> 00:07:29.520
DR. GRIFFITHS:
Well, of course,
my darling.

110
00:07:29.560 --> 00:07:32.360
LIZZY: Look at
the creek and the woods
and the meadow!

111
00:07:32.440 --> 00:07:33.520
(DR. GRIFFITHS LAUGHS)

112
00:07:33.560 --> 00:07:36.080
Oh! I wish it was
summer all year long!

113
00:07:36.360 --> 00:07:38.560
(LAUGHS)
Yes, Lizzy.

114
00:07:48.960 --> 00:07:50.120
(TINKER BELL GASPS)

115
00:08:02.320 --> 00:08:04.880
Tinker Bell,
what are you
doing here?

116
00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:09.080
Vidia, this is amazing!
It's a carriage
that moves by itself!

117
00:08:09.440 --> 00:08:11.400
There's no horse.
Seriously, look.

118
00:08:11.480 --> 00:08:12.560
Do you see a horse
up there?

119
00:08:12.600 --> 00:08:13.600
Uh. No.

120
00:08:13.680 --> 00:08:17.800
It's a horseless carriage!
And do you want to
know how it works?

121
00:08:17.880 --> 00:08:19.680
Not really.
So do I.

122
00:08:19.880 --> 00:08:21.880
I think those wheels
back there move

123
00:08:21.920 --> 00:08:24.080
because this
chain thing rotates.

124
00:08:24.560 --> 00:08:27.160
And I think what
rotates the chain
is this big...

125
00:08:27.240 --> 00:08:28.320
I don't care, Tinker Bell.

126
00:08:28.440 --> 00:08:30.960
You shouldn't
be this close to
the human house.

127
00:08:31.040 --> 00:08:32.800
What if they see us?

128
00:08:34.680 --> 00:08:35.800
(GASPS)

129
00:08:36.160 --> 00:08:39.640
Will you stop
flitting around in there?
This is serious!

130
00:08:40.200 --> 00:08:43.800
You know what, Vidia?
I think this powers
the whole thing!

131
00:08:43.880 --> 00:08:44.960
(GRUMBLES)

132
00:08:46.760 --> 00:08:49.960
This, my dear,
is exactly why tinkers

133
00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:52.160
shouldn't come to
the mainland. They...

134
00:08:52.560 --> 00:08:53.680
(COUGHING)

135
00:08:53.800 --> 00:08:55.280
Let me know if
this does anything.

136
00:08:55.600 --> 00:08:56.760
(GROANS)

137
00:08:57.120 --> 00:08:58.280
(COUGHING)

138
00:08:58.760 --> 00:09:02.160
Well, anything?
Vidia, you're all wet.

139
00:09:03.640 --> 00:09:05.120
You don't say.

140
00:09:05.160 --> 00:09:08.600
LIZZY: Father, Father, Father!
Can we bring our tea
and scones outside

141
00:09:08.640 --> 00:09:10.160
and have them
here in the garden?

142
00:09:10.240 --> 00:09:11.640
It would be just
like a little picnic.

143
00:09:11.720 --> 00:09:12.840
DR. GRIFFITHS:
Not just now, Lizzy.

144
00:09:12.920 --> 00:09:15.640
I still have to get
the trunk unpacked
and the house settled.

145
00:09:15.720 --> 00:09:18.960
(GASPS) Father, look!
What a magnificent butterfly.

146
00:09:21.160 --> 00:09:25.720
My word.
Absolutely astonishing.

147
00:09:25.800 --> 00:09:28.880
It's so beautiful.
What kind of
butterfly is it?

148
00:09:29.480 --> 00:09:33.520
Well, judging from
the epidermal membrane,
it's clearly an <i>apatura iris,</i>

149
00:09:33.600 --> 00:09:37.040
but the wings
have two entirely
different patterns.

150
00:09:37.480 --> 00:09:39.600
Well, that's
nearly impossible.

151
00:09:39.680 --> 00:09:41.000
Well, I guess
that's just the way

152
00:09:41.040 --> 00:09:43.200
the fairies
decided to paint it.

153
00:09:43.280 --> 00:09:44.280
Hmm?

154
00:09:44.320 --> 00:09:46.360
Lizzy,
fairies do not paint
butterfly wings

155
00:09:46.840 --> 00:09:50.040
because, as you know,
fairies are not real.

156
00:09:50.280 --> 00:09:51.280
Hmm!
Ugh!

157
00:09:51.360 --> 00:09:53.640
But of course they are.
The proof is right here.

158
00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:55.880
Their paint dripped
all over its wing.

159
00:09:55.960 --> 00:09:57.360
Really, darling.

160
00:09:57.400 --> 00:10:01.400
Rational people consider
a belief in fairies
to be quite foolish.

161
00:10:01.520 --> 00:10:02.680
DR. GRIFFITHS:
The wings are so fresh.

162
00:10:02.720 --> 00:10:04.000
What are you doing?

163
00:10:04.080 --> 00:10:06.160
Its chrysalis
must have been
in the meadow.

164
00:10:06.200 --> 00:10:08.960
The meadow?
Father, wait!

165
00:10:10.720 --> 00:10:13.640
That's where I'm going.
Would you like to come?

166
00:10:13.680 --> 00:10:15.920
Not now, Lizzy.
I have to update
my field journal.

167
00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:18.600
My interview at the museum
is tomorrow night.

168
00:10:18.720 --> 00:10:22.040
You're going back already?
We just got here.

169
00:10:23.080 --> 00:10:25.880
I know, sweetheart,
and I'm very sorry.

170
00:10:25.960 --> 00:10:27.600
But I'll only be
gone for the day.

171
00:10:27.760 --> 00:10:29.560
Mrs. Perkins
will look after you,

172
00:10:29.640 --> 00:10:31.880
and I'll be back
in time to tuck you in.

173
00:10:31.960 --> 00:10:33.160
Promise?

174
00:10:33.200 --> 00:10:34.400
I promise.

175
00:10:35.920 --> 00:10:37.040
Okay.

176
00:10:37.080 --> 00:10:38.160
That's a good girl.

177
00:10:40.240 --> 00:10:41.400
(SIGHING)

178
00:10:49.240 --> 00:10:50.560
All clear!

179
00:10:52.200 --> 00:10:53.320
Come on, Vidia.

180
00:10:53.400 --> 00:10:56.360
(SIGHS) I can't fly.
My wings are wet.

181
00:10:56.400 --> 00:10:58.240
Oh! That's right. Sorry.

182
00:10:59.280 --> 00:11:01.560
Guess you'll
have to walk back.

183
00:11:02.760 --> 00:11:06.960
But don't worry,
I'll keep you company.
Actually, it might be nice.

184
00:11:07.760 --> 00:11:08.880
(SIGHS)

185
00:11:10.880 --> 00:11:14.520
Or not.
So, I think I figured
out the carriage.

186
00:11:14.840 --> 00:11:16.920
Those bottles of goop
must keep it
running smoothly,

187
00:11:16.960 --> 00:11:19.080
like snail slime,
you know?

188
00:11:19.160 --> 00:11:21.520
Hate to see the size
of the snail that
stuff comes from.

189
00:11:21.600 --> 00:11:22.640
And at first...

190
00:11:46.800 --> 00:11:47.920
(INHALING DEEPLY)

191
00:12:00.880 --> 00:12:04.160
Here's your house,
little fairies.
Wherever you are.

192
00:12:07.280 --> 00:12:10.520
Hmm. Just needs
a little something more.

193
00:12:13.760 --> 00:12:17.480
But I haven't quite
figured out what that
sparky wire does.

194
00:12:17.600 --> 00:12:21.200
Hey! Maybe the whole carriage
runs on lightning!

195
00:12:22.600 --> 00:12:23.960
(GROANS IN FRUSTRATION)

196
00:12:24.440 --> 00:12:28.840
Are those wet wings
still bugging you?
Here, Vidia, let me help you.

197
00:12:29.160 --> 00:12:30.200
(SCOFFS)

198
00:12:30.280 --> 00:12:34.160
Tinker Bell, maybe if
you spent less time
causing disasters,

199
00:12:34.200 --> 00:12:37.880
you wouldn't have to help
everybody so much.

200
00:12:38.040 --> 00:12:39.480
(GASPS) Whoa!

201
00:12:39.560 --> 00:12:41.160
Hmm. The truth hurts,
doesn't it?

202
00:12:41.280 --> 00:12:44.240
Look! We can use
these back at camp!

203
00:12:44.680 --> 00:12:45.680
(GROANS)

204
00:12:45.760 --> 00:12:49.040
Wow. These'll be perfect
for the new wagon prototype
I've been working on.

205
00:12:49.160 --> 00:12:52.000
Here. I bet if I
took two or three
and tied them together,

206
00:12:52.080 --> 00:12:54.640
I could make one
really strong wheel!

207
00:12:54.680 --> 00:12:55.920
It's a good thing
we were walking

208
00:12:56.000 --> 00:12:58.880
or we might never
have seen these.

209
00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:01.200
Vidia, where are
your buttons?

210
00:13:01.600 --> 00:13:05.680
Tinker Bell,
I am not carrying this
human junk back to camp.

211
00:13:06.520 --> 00:13:07.680
(BOTH GASP)

212
00:13:13.560 --> 00:13:14.720
Ah!

213
00:13:14.800 --> 00:13:16.560
Let's go!
Let's go!

214
00:13:19.960 --> 00:13:24.240
Tinker Bell,
we're not supposed
to go near human houses.

215
00:13:24.320 --> 00:13:27.040
This isn't a human house.
They're a lot bigger.

216
00:13:27.080 --> 00:13:29.720
Besides, the sign says,
"Fairies welcome."

217
00:13:29.800 --> 00:13:32.480
Who do you think wrote it?
Humans!

218
00:13:34.640 --> 00:13:37.320
Tinker Bell,
you're not going in there.

219
00:13:39.080 --> 00:13:42.680
Please tell me
you're not going in there!
She went in there.

220
00:13:45.240 --> 00:13:46.400
TINKER BELL: Oh!

221
00:13:50.920 --> 00:13:51.960
Wow.

222
00:13:59.320 --> 00:14:00.400
(SNIFFING)

223
00:14:00.440 --> 00:14:04.040
Tinker Bell!
Don't eat that!
This could be a trap.

224
00:14:04.720 --> 00:14:07.280
Come on, Vidia.
It's perfectly safe.

225
00:14:07.560 --> 00:14:08.760
Oh, really?

226
00:14:12.320 --> 00:14:13.440
(GASPS)

227
00:14:13.920 --> 00:14:15.200
Oh, Vidia.

228
00:14:15.280 --> 00:14:17.600
Huh! Not so safe now,
is it?

229
00:14:18.120 --> 00:14:20.880
Nice try, Vidia,
but you're not scaring me.

230
00:14:20.960 --> 00:14:22.600
Gosh,
this thing is amazing.

231
00:14:22.640 --> 00:14:24.680
You just don't
know when to stop,
do you?

232
00:14:24.800 --> 00:14:25.920
(RUSTLING)

233
00:14:25.960 --> 00:14:27.080
(GASPING)

234
00:14:28.440 --> 00:14:31.000
Oh, no. Tink!
Someone's coming!

235
00:14:31.440 --> 00:14:32.480
(GRUNTING)

236
00:14:32.560 --> 00:14:34.280
The door is stuck!

237
00:14:34.360 --> 00:14:36.480
Come on, Vidia.
You can do better than that.

238
00:14:36.480 --> 00:14:37.560
VIDIA: Tink!

239
00:14:37.640 --> 00:14:38.840
I wonder what
this part does.

240
00:14:38.920 --> 00:14:41.880
Tink! I'm serious!
Get out of there!

241
00:14:41.960 --> 00:14:43.880
Just a second.
Just a second.

242
00:14:46.160 --> 00:14:47.280
(GASPING)

243
00:14:51.560 --> 00:14:52.640
(CLOCK TICKING)

244
00:14:54.160 --> 00:14:57.120
Vidia? Vidia?

245
00:15:00.640 --> 00:15:03.600
Oh, Vidia, come on.
Open the door.
You had your little...

246
00:15:03.640 --> 00:15:05.240
(TINKER BELL'S
BELL JINGLING)

247
00:15:05.320 --> 00:15:06.440
(GASPING)

248
00:15:08.880 --> 00:15:11.440
Oh, no.
What have I done?

249
00:15:12.040 --> 00:15:15.360
Vidia? Okay,
not funny anymore.

250
00:15:18.200 --> 00:15:19.440
(SCREAMING)

251
00:15:20.400 --> 00:15:21.720
(GASPING)

252
00:15:22.000 --> 00:15:23.600
A fairy!

253
00:15:27.440 --> 00:15:30.080
It's a real fairy!

254
00:15:35.560 --> 00:15:37.680
Father! Father!

255
00:15:41.240 --> 00:15:42.400
(SCREAMING)

256
00:15:43.920 --> 00:15:45.080
Father!

257
00:15:51.560 --> 00:15:52.720
(SNIFFING)

258
00:15:56.280 --> 00:15:57.640
Father! Father, Father!

259
00:15:57.720 --> 00:15:58.840
Yes, Lizzy.

260
00:15:59.120 --> 00:16:00.960
You're never
going to believe
what I found.

261
00:16:01.040 --> 00:16:02.600
Maybe later, Lizzy.

262
00:16:02.680 --> 00:16:04.920
But Father,
Father, Father,

263
00:16:05.000 --> 00:16:06.760
Father, Father.
Just a moment, dear.

264
00:16:06.800 --> 00:16:08.240
I'm very busy
with my project.

265
00:16:08.320 --> 00:16:09.760
Yes, but Father!

266
00:16:09.800 --> 00:16:11.320
Father!
Lizzy, please.

267
00:16:11.400 --> 00:16:15.120
I must add this
extraordinary discovery
to my field journal.

268
00:16:15.240 --> 00:16:16.760
And here it is.

269
00:16:16.960 --> 00:16:18.080
(LIZZY GASPING)

270
00:16:18.280 --> 00:16:20.920
Is that the butterfly
we were looking at earlier?

271
00:16:21.040 --> 00:16:23.760
Yes. Quite a specimen,
isn't it?

272
00:16:23.800 --> 00:16:26.000
LIZZY: You're not going to
take it to London, are you?

273
00:16:26.080 --> 00:16:27.120
DR. GRIFFITHS:
Yes, of course.

274
00:16:27.200 --> 00:16:28.880
The board of trustees
would never believe me

275
00:16:28.960 --> 00:16:30.160
if they didn't
see it themselves.

276
00:16:30.240 --> 00:16:32.920
Now I'm sure to
get that curatorship
at the museum.

277
00:16:32.960 --> 00:16:35.160
Besides, as a member
of the scientific community,

278
00:16:35.240 --> 00:16:39.240
I'm obligated to share
significant findings like this
with my colleagues.

279
00:16:39.280 --> 00:16:41.440
I know it's unfortunate
for the specimen,

280
00:16:41.520 --> 00:16:43.640
but really,
there is no other way.

281
00:16:43.680 --> 00:16:45.800
Now, dear.
What did you
want me to see?

282
00:16:45.960 --> 00:16:47.000
Uh...

283
00:16:47.080 --> 00:16:48.480
Never mind.

284
00:17:11.640 --> 00:17:13.400
Where have you gone?

285
00:17:26.920 --> 00:17:28.080
(GROWLING)

286
00:17:28.520 --> 00:17:31.840
Mr. Twitches, no!
Out! Out with you!

287
00:17:35.480 --> 00:17:37.200
Mr. Twitches!

288
00:17:42.480 --> 00:17:45.200
Bad cat! No, no, no!

289
00:17:45.520 --> 00:17:47.000
(MR. TWITCHES GROWLING)

290
00:17:49.040 --> 00:17:50.960
Don't worry, little fairy.

291
00:17:51.040 --> 00:17:53.760
Mr. Twitches won't bother you
as long as you're in there.

292
00:17:53.880 --> 00:17:55.160
(SNARLING)

293
00:17:55.240 --> 00:17:58.160
Naughty cat!
You're going outside.

294
00:18:04.560 --> 00:18:05.640
(STRAINING)

295
00:18:35.400 --> 00:18:37.080
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

296
00:18:37.680 --> 00:18:39.160
(TINKER BELL WHIMPERING)

297
00:19:17.480 --> 00:19:19.120
Tinker Bell's
been captured by humans!

298
00:19:19.280 --> 00:19:20.400
(ALL GASPING)

299
00:19:20.440 --> 00:19:21.680
Oh, no.
What happened?
Is she okay?

300
00:19:21.800 --> 00:19:23.040
Is she all right?
What's this? Tinker Bell?

301
00:19:23.120 --> 00:19:24.640
What happened, Vidia?
Is she hurt?

302
00:19:24.680 --> 00:19:26.920
Tinker Bell went
into this little house
in the meadow

303
00:19:26.960 --> 00:19:28.200
and couldn't get out.

304
00:19:28.280 --> 00:19:30.080
The door got jammed.

305
00:19:30.320 --> 00:19:33.120
Then this human came
from out of nowhere
and snatched her up,

306
00:19:33.160 --> 00:19:36.080
but I know where she is.
We have to hurry
and save her.

307
00:19:36.120 --> 00:19:38.480
Then we better
leave right away!

308
00:19:43.000 --> 00:19:44.960
Sil, do you think the storm
will pass soon?

309
00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:47.600
No, it looks like
it's gonna get stronger.

310
00:19:47.640 --> 00:19:49.760
Well, there's gotta be
some way to get to Tink.

311
00:19:49.800 --> 00:19:52.880
We can't fly in the rain,
and the meadow's
already flooded.

312
00:19:52.960 --> 00:19:54.680
Maybe we don't
have to fly.

313
00:19:54.760 --> 00:19:58.880
If we get some big leaves
and sew them together
with stem twine...

314
00:19:59.200 --> 00:20:01.320
And miter-cut some twigs
for the sub-flooring.

315
00:20:01.400 --> 00:20:02.840
Acorns as counterweights.

316
00:20:02.880 --> 00:20:05.200
Some quick-dry maple sap
as reinforcement.

317
00:20:05.280 --> 00:20:06.840
What are you two
talking about?

318
00:20:06.880 --> 00:20:10.000
We're gonna build a boat!
We're gonna build a boat!

319
00:20:19.000 --> 00:20:21.600
CLANK: More
mushroom caps, please!

320
00:20:21.680 --> 00:20:22.840
Here we go.

321
00:20:25.040 --> 00:20:28.600
BOBBLE: This one goes there.
That one goes there. Right?

322
00:20:30.000 --> 00:20:31.840
CLANK: Righty-o, Bobble.

323
00:20:31.920 --> 00:20:33.040
(CLANK CHUCKLES)

324
00:20:33.120 --> 00:20:34.240
(WHISTLING)

325
00:20:34.760 --> 00:20:35.960
(ALL STRAINING)

326
00:20:36.560 --> 00:20:37.760
(SQUEAKING)

327
00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:39.200
(GRUNTING)

328
00:20:45.120 --> 00:20:46.720
CLANK: Right,
more reeds over here.

329
00:20:46.800 --> 00:20:48.320
This thing had better work.

330
00:20:48.360 --> 00:20:49.800
BOBBLE: Give me the sap.
You dip it in this way

331
00:20:49.880 --> 00:20:52.680
and give it
a big slap like so.

332
00:20:54.880 --> 00:20:57.800
Ow. Ow. Ow.

333
00:20:57.880 --> 00:21:00.320
CLANK: Come on. Come on.
Let's get going.

334
00:21:00.560 --> 00:21:01.800
(BUZZING)

335
00:21:02.840 --> 00:21:05.240
BOBBLE: There you go.
Now you're talking!

336
00:21:12.240 --> 00:21:13.720
CLANK: It's working!

337
00:21:22.040 --> 00:21:23.480
Well, this is it.

338
00:21:26.840 --> 00:21:28.360
Hey, faith...

339
00:21:28.760 --> 00:21:29.960
Trust...

340
00:21:30.040 --> 00:21:31.640
And pixie dust.
Pixie dust.

341
00:21:37.920 --> 00:21:39.760
Come on. Come on.

342
00:21:40.000 --> 00:21:41.480
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

343
00:21:46.360 --> 00:21:47.560
Hello.

344
00:21:51.600 --> 00:21:55.400
You don't have to be scared.
I'm very nice.

345
00:21:59.120 --> 00:22:00.760
You're so little.

346
00:22:01.360 --> 00:22:05.320
Your dress is very leafy.
Did you make it yourself?

347
00:22:06.120 --> 00:22:09.200
I like your wings.
They're like
sparkly lace.

348
00:22:09.760 --> 00:22:11.800
Your hair must be so soft.

349
00:22:14.040 --> 00:22:18.600
Are you hungry?
Maybe not.
That's okay.

350
00:22:18.800 --> 00:22:21.360
I don't like some
kinds of food, either.

351
00:22:23.200 --> 00:22:24.360
Oh!

352
00:22:24.440 --> 00:22:27.440
I'm so sorry.
Where are my manners?

353
00:22:28.960 --> 00:22:30.400
There you go.

354
00:22:37.680 --> 00:22:43.160
Wait!
Wait! Wait! No, please!
I'm not going to hurt you!

355
00:22:44.800 --> 00:22:48.880
Don't be afraid!
I just want to
be your friend!

356
00:22:50.880 --> 00:22:55.720
I really won't hurt you.
I just love fairies.

357
00:22:56.920 --> 00:22:59.840
I've been drawing fairies
all my life. See?

358
00:23:00.800 --> 00:23:02.960
I drew that one
when I was three,

359
00:23:03.000 --> 00:23:05.000
but I did that
green one last week.

360
00:23:05.400 --> 00:23:08.160
(CHUCKLES) I think
it's much better.

361
00:23:08.800 --> 00:23:12.520
I even started to paint
with the watercolors
Father gave me.

362
00:23:14.360 --> 00:23:17.200
Is it true that some fairies
paint butterfly wings?

363
00:23:20.040 --> 00:23:21.360
I knew it!

364
00:23:22.040 --> 00:23:24.640
These are some
of my favorite drawings.

365
00:23:24.880 --> 00:23:26.400
This is a water fairy.

366
00:23:26.480 --> 00:23:28.440
You can tell because
her skin is blue.

367
00:23:28.520 --> 00:23:29.680
Blue?

368
00:23:29.920 --> 00:23:33.160
And here is a candy fairy
living in a lollipop tree.

369
00:23:33.200 --> 00:23:35.200
Do all fairies live in trees
made of sweets?

370
00:23:37.880 --> 00:23:41.040
Really?
What about fairy circles?

371
00:23:43.240 --> 00:23:45.920
Well, I hear
that if a person
steps in one,

372
00:23:46.000 --> 00:23:49.680
a fairy has to
grant them three wishes
from their magic bag.

373
00:23:50.440 --> 00:23:54.040
But if they don't,
they turn into a pile
of delicious sugar,

374
00:23:54.080 --> 00:23:55.400
and then
younger fairies...
(LAUGHS) Wait. Wait a minute.

375
00:23:55.440 --> 00:23:56.440
...must try and
turn them back into...

376
00:23:56.520 --> 00:23:58.240
Where are you
getting all this?

377
00:23:58.280 --> 00:24:00.280
(BELL JINGLING)

378
00:24:00.640 --> 00:24:04.160
(GASPS) You
jingle when you talk,
like a little bell!

379
00:24:04.400 --> 00:24:06.560
So that's how fairies speak.

380
00:24:06.720 --> 00:24:08.120
(BELL JINGLING)

381
00:24:08.280 --> 00:24:11.760
So what do you
think of my fairies?
Oh! And my fairy house!

382
00:24:15.080 --> 00:24:17.080
It got a little shaken up.

383
00:24:22.360 --> 00:24:24.240
Did you make this?
(BELL JINGLING)

384
00:24:24.320 --> 00:24:26.120
I don't know
what you're saying.

385
00:24:31.520 --> 00:24:36.400
Oh.
Did I make the fairy house?
Yes, I did. Do you like it?

386
00:24:40.120 --> 00:24:42.440
Oh. The door's stuck.

387
00:24:49.440 --> 00:24:52.600
Well, you're quite
the little tinker,
aren't you?

388
00:24:52.960 --> 00:24:56.440
What? Is that your name?
Tinker?

389
00:24:58.840 --> 00:24:59.840
Er...

390
00:24:59.920 --> 00:25:02.880
Bell? Your name is Bell.

391
00:25:05.760 --> 00:25:08.240
Tinker? Bell?

392
00:25:10.160 --> 00:25:13.760
Tinker Bell? Tinker Bell.

393
00:25:15.000 --> 00:25:20.280
What a lovely name!
Well, Tinker Bell,
my name's Lizzy.

394
00:25:24.760 --> 00:25:27.640
LIZZY: Do all fairies
sound the same
when they talk?

395
00:25:27.680 --> 00:25:28.880
(WATER DRIPPING)

396
00:25:28.920 --> 00:25:31.760
How do you
learn to be a fairy?
Do you go to fairy school?

397
00:25:31.840 --> 00:25:32.840
DR. GRIFFITHS:
Lizzy?

398
00:25:32.880 --> 00:25:33.920
(LIZZY GASPING)

399
00:25:34.000 --> 00:25:36.760
Lizzy?
Who are you talking to?

400
00:25:38.440 --> 00:25:39.880
Oh. Um...

401
00:25:40.760 --> 00:25:42.040
My fairy!

402
00:25:44.040 --> 00:25:45.640
That's nice, dear.
Now, I brought you

403
00:25:45.720 --> 00:25:48.560
something I think
you'll really enjoy.

404
00:25:48.640 --> 00:25:52.000
These are some of my
old field journals.

405
00:25:52.520 --> 00:25:55.000
Now, I picked out the ones
I thought would excite you
the most.

406
00:25:55.040 --> 00:25:59.440
This one
on rocks and minerals
is particularly interesting.

407
00:25:59.640 --> 00:26:01.840
Is there a field journal
about fairies?

408
00:26:01.880 --> 00:26:04.080
(LAUGHS)
Of course not, Lizzy.

409
00:26:04.560 --> 00:26:08.240
Books like this
are based on fact
and scientific research,

410
00:26:08.880 --> 00:26:10.160
which is the quite
the contrary

411
00:26:10.240 --> 00:26:12.040
to your little
figurines and drawings.

412
00:26:12.080 --> 00:26:14.240
Well,
just because you've
never seen a fairy

413
00:26:14.320 --> 00:26:16.200
doesn't mean
they're not real.

414
00:26:16.240 --> 00:26:19.600
Now, Lizzy,
seeing is believing,

415
00:26:19.600 --> 00:26:22.480
and without proof,
it's just a fairy tale.

416
00:26:22.840 --> 00:26:26.560
Now, here is
a blank field journal.

417
00:26:26.600 --> 00:26:28.160
Now, you're very talented,
my darling,

418
00:26:28.720 --> 00:26:30.040
and I'm sure you'll
be able to fill it

419
00:26:30.080 --> 00:26:33.000
with your own
scientific research.

420
00:26:33.080 --> 00:26:34.480
Yes, Father.

421
00:26:36.160 --> 00:26:37.280
(WATER DRIPPING)

422
00:26:37.360 --> 00:26:40.800
(SIGHS) Now if
only these leaks
were just pretend.

423
00:26:42.840 --> 00:26:45.280
Tinker Bell,
you can come out now.

424
00:26:49.120 --> 00:26:52.640
Look, Lizzy,
thanks for showing me
your collection,

425
00:26:52.720 --> 00:26:54.960
but I really should be...

426
00:26:55.280 --> 00:26:56.640
(BELL JINGLING)

427
00:26:57.080 --> 00:26:58.600
You want to go?

428
00:26:59.600 --> 00:27:02.400
Oh. I really wish
you'd stay.

429
00:27:03.360 --> 00:27:04.800
I'm sorry, Lizzy.

430
00:27:06.080 --> 00:27:08.360
Okay, I understand.

431
00:27:16.120 --> 00:27:18.240
So, I guess
this is goodbye.

432
00:27:22.880 --> 00:27:25.160
What's wrong?
Can't you fly in the rain?

433
00:27:27.200 --> 00:27:28.240
(GASPS)

434
00:27:28.320 --> 00:27:30.760
You can stay with me
until the rain stops.

435
00:27:30.800 --> 00:27:34.320
I'll show you around my room.
We can play with my toys.

436
00:27:34.360 --> 00:27:36.280
We'll have so much fun.

437
00:27:43.320 --> 00:27:45.080
We're past the shallows!

438
00:27:45.160 --> 00:27:47.240
Aye! Drop the mainsail!

439
00:27:47.520 --> 00:27:49.320
Dropping the mainsail!

440
00:27:50.120 --> 00:27:51.320
Trim the sail!

441
00:27:51.360 --> 00:27:52.560
Trimming the sail!

442
00:27:56.760 --> 00:28:00.520
Big thingy, dead ahead!
Hard to port!

443
00:28:00.600 --> 00:28:02.240
Hard to port!
Hard to port!

444
00:28:09.520 --> 00:28:12.440
I recognize that wagon.
Stay on this course!

445
00:28:12.680 --> 00:28:14.520
Aye, Miss Vidia.
Will do.

446
00:28:14.600 --> 00:28:16.440
I sure hope
Tink is all right.

447
00:28:16.640 --> 00:28:18.120
Who knows what
terrible things

448
00:28:18.200 --> 00:28:20.160
could be happening
to her right now.

449
00:28:21.000 --> 00:28:22.040
(SIGHING)

450
00:28:22.640 --> 00:28:24.960
A fairy could
get used to this.

451
00:28:25.040 --> 00:28:26.880
Isn't it wonderful?

452
00:28:26.920 --> 00:28:29.960
Everything in this house
is just your size,
Tinker Bell.

453
00:28:32.120 --> 00:28:34.920
That's perfume.
It smells like flowers.

454
00:28:36.400 --> 00:28:39.480
Oh. My doll.
She should be
in bed by now.

455
00:28:40.720 --> 00:28:42.800
How old are you? I'm nine.

456
00:28:44.560 --> 00:28:48.560
Do you like my dollhouse?
Do fairies live in houses?

457
00:28:49.880 --> 00:28:52.320
What are
fairies' houses made of?

458
00:28:52.880 --> 00:28:55.720
That's a cooker,
but it doesn't
actually work.

459
00:28:55.800 --> 00:28:59.560
What's your favorite food?
I mean, besides sweets?

460
00:29:00.640 --> 00:29:03.600
I want to know all about
real live fairies.

461
00:29:10.800 --> 00:29:12.040
Perfect!

462
00:29:14.160 --> 00:29:18.920
"Scientific fairy research."

463
00:29:19.920 --> 00:29:22.360
Okay. What's your
favorite color?

464
00:29:24.960 --> 00:29:27.320
Green is my
favorite color, too!

465
00:29:29.000 --> 00:29:30.760
I should start
from the beginning.

466
00:29:30.840 --> 00:29:32.840
Where do fairies
come from?

467
00:29:32.960 --> 00:29:34.840
I mean,
where were you born?

468
00:29:34.960 --> 00:29:36.040
Oh.

469
00:29:36.120 --> 00:29:39.440
Well, that one's
a little more
complicated because...

470
00:29:39.840 --> 00:29:41.760
So, a baby, when it laughs
for the first time...

471
00:29:41.920 --> 00:29:43.360
(BELL JINGLING)

472
00:29:44.560 --> 00:29:45.920
A fairy...

473
00:29:47.000 --> 00:29:48.000
Uh... Uh...

474
00:29:48.080 --> 00:29:49.120
Oh.

475
00:29:49.200 --> 00:29:51.960
Right. One second.

476
00:29:57.680 --> 00:30:00.120
You were
a funny-looking baby?

477
00:30:03.200 --> 00:30:04.440
A baby?

478
00:30:07.480 --> 00:30:08.480
Laughs?

479
00:30:11.840 --> 00:30:12.920
One?

480
00:30:15.760 --> 00:30:16.960
First?

481
00:30:17.160 --> 00:30:23.640
When a baby laughs
for the first time,
that's when a fairy is born.

482
00:30:26.280 --> 00:30:27.680
Incredible.

483
00:30:29.160 --> 00:30:31.600
Lizzy, that's only
the beginning.

484
00:30:31.680 --> 00:30:32.680
<i>(HOW TO BELIEVE</i> PLAYING)

485
00:30:32.800 --> 00:30:35.320
<i>WOMAN: ♪ Guess I always knew</i>

486
00:30:35.840 --> 00:30:40.000
<i>♪ This could all come true</i>

