Oh. I'm good.

542
00:34:37.360 --> 00:34:38.360
(GROANING)

543
00:34:38.440 --> 00:34:39.480
(EXCLAIMS)

544
00:34:39.600 --> 00:34:40.800
Oh!

545
00:34:41.600 --> 00:34:42.680
(SCREAMING) Ow!

546
00:34:42.760 --> 00:34:44.800
Oh! Sorry!

547
00:34:44.960 --> 00:34:46.000
Ow!

548
00:34:46.880 --> 00:34:49.080
Looks like we're
walking from here.

549
00:34:49.640 --> 00:34:52.480
But... Walking where?

550
00:34:52.520 --> 00:34:53.720
We could be anywhere.

551
00:34:54.400 --> 00:34:57.120
Everything looks the same
from down here.

552
00:34:57.480 --> 00:35:00.480
And there's
no way of knowing
which way to go.

553
00:35:00.560 --> 00:35:03.200
Clank!
Where did you find that?

554
00:35:04.440 --> 00:35:08.000
I don't know.
Here on the ground.
Is it yours?

555
00:35:18.040 --> 00:35:19.840
I know where we are.

556
00:35:23.120 --> 00:35:26.880
Tinker Bell,
this is so fascinating.
Thank you.

557
00:35:27.640 --> 00:35:31.600
I had no idea
fairies were responsible
for changing the seasons.

558
00:35:32.160 --> 00:35:34.840
I thought it had
something to do
with the Earth's axis

559
00:35:34.880 --> 00:35:36.800
as it rotated
around the sun.

560
00:35:36.840 --> 00:35:39.200
(LAUGHS) That's what
we wanted you to think.

561
00:35:39.920 --> 00:35:42.640
Well, I think we've
covered everything.

562
00:35:42.680 --> 00:35:45.360
Oh. I hope
Father's impressed.

563
00:35:46.000 --> 00:35:48.360
And now, for the finale.

564
00:35:49.520 --> 00:35:52.560
The whole fairy land,
Pixie Hollow.

565
00:35:57.040 --> 00:36:01.360
It worked! Tinker Bell,
I can't wait to show Father.

566
00:36:03.160 --> 00:36:07.880
Tinker Bell?
Are you all right?
Tinker Bell?

567
00:36:07.960 --> 00:36:09.120
Huh?

568
00:36:09.200 --> 00:36:12.600
Oh. Sorry. Yeah,
let's go show your dad.

569
00:36:15.880 --> 00:36:17.160
(SIGHING)

570
00:36:26.400 --> 00:36:28.920
Looks like the rain
has let up some.

571
00:36:29.400 --> 00:36:32.080
You might be
able to make it home
to your friends now.

572
00:36:36.800 --> 00:36:38.880
Maybe this could help you.

573
00:36:43.720 --> 00:36:45.120
Oh, yes.

574
00:36:49.920 --> 00:36:51.360
Such a clever tinker.

575
00:36:51.440 --> 00:36:52.520
(SNIFFLES)

576
00:36:55.960 --> 00:36:57.840
Take care of yourself.

577
00:37:07.760 --> 00:37:10.280
I'll never forget you,
Tinker Bell.

578
00:37:14.400 --> 00:37:18.200
You'd best hurry.
The break in the weather
may not last long.

579
00:37:25.120 --> 00:37:26.280
(SNIFFLING)

580
00:37:36.880 --> 00:37:37.880
Goodbye.

581
00:37:44.240 --> 00:37:46.640
And I'll never
forget you, Lizzy.

582
00:37:51.520 --> 00:37:53.560
LIZZY: Father, look!

583
00:37:53.640 --> 00:37:54.680
DR. GRIFFITHS:
Not just now, Lizzy.

584
00:37:54.760 --> 00:37:56.800
My hands are rather
full at the moment.

585
00:37:56.880 --> 00:37:59.160
I made it especially
for you, Father.

586
00:37:59.200 --> 00:38:01.160
It's just like
your field journal.

587
00:38:01.240 --> 00:38:02.640
It's filled with
lots of facts.

588
00:38:02.720 --> 00:38:03.960
Yes, yes,
that sounds wonderful,

589
00:38:04.000 --> 00:38:06.760
but I'm in the middle
of a potential
catastrophe here.

590
00:38:06.840 --> 00:38:08.160
I can't look at it now.

591
00:38:08.200 --> 00:38:10.360
But Father,
it's a field journal,
and I...

592
00:38:10.440 --> 00:38:11.520
I don't have time.

593
00:38:11.600 --> 00:38:14.160
I have to find some way
to deal with all these leaks

594
00:38:14.200 --> 00:38:16.080
before they
destroy my work.

595
00:38:16.160 --> 00:38:18.200
When will you be
able to look at it?

596
00:38:18.280 --> 00:38:21.280
(GROANS) I don't know.
Maybe later.

597
00:38:22.440 --> 00:38:24.160
You always say that.

598
00:38:33.600 --> 00:38:34.680
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

599
00:39:04.600 --> 00:39:05.760
(SNIFFLING)

600
00:39:12.240 --> 00:39:13.560
(GASPS)

601
00:39:13.720 --> 00:39:14.960
Tinker Bell!

602
00:39:17.480 --> 00:39:21.280
You came back!
I'm so glad to see you.

603
00:39:24.880 --> 00:39:28.480
Tinker Bell,
Father has no time
for the field journal.

604
00:39:31.960 --> 00:39:33.880
I think I can fix that.

605
00:39:36.120 --> 00:39:38.600
ROSETTA:
Vidia, you sure you know
where you're going?

606
00:39:38.680 --> 00:39:41.360
VIDIA: Yes. Tinker Bell
and I walked by here.

607
00:39:41.440 --> 00:39:43.000
I just have to
find the road.

608
00:39:43.240 --> 00:39:44.840
FAWN: Road? What road?

609
00:39:46.080 --> 00:39:47.120
(GASPS)

610
00:39:47.200 --> 00:39:48.600
That road!

611
00:39:50.000 --> 00:39:53.200
That's not a road.
That's a muddy river.

612
00:39:53.280 --> 00:39:55.840
So, I guess we need
to find a bridge.

613
00:39:56.760 --> 00:39:59.400
Or be spontaneous
and jump right in.

614
00:40:00.040 --> 00:40:02.440
It's not deep.
We can walk across.

615
00:40:04.720 --> 00:40:07.520
Yeah, no.
I don't really do mud.

616
00:40:08.560 --> 00:40:11.560
But you're a garden fairy!

617
00:40:11.600 --> 00:40:13.200
(LAUGHS)
Ironic, isn't it?

618
00:40:13.400 --> 00:40:14.560
ALL: Rosetta!

619
00:40:14.640 --> 00:40:16.760
Okay, all right.
I'm coming.

620
00:40:21.320 --> 00:40:24.640
It's squishy.
Oh! What was that?

621
00:40:24.760 --> 00:40:25.880
(GROANING)

622
00:40:27.280 --> 00:40:28.320
(GASPING)

623
00:40:30.120 --> 00:40:31.320
(STRAINING)

624
00:40:32.480 --> 00:40:33.760
She's stuck!

625
00:40:34.200 --> 00:40:36.520
I can get myself
out of here.

626
00:40:38.000 --> 00:40:39.320
(GROANS)

627
00:40:39.400 --> 00:40:40.840
All right, all right.

628
00:40:40.960 --> 00:40:43.440
Someone just
get me something
to grab onto.

629
