Got it!
Clanky, rescue device.

630
00:40:45.560 --> 00:40:48.320
Right, Bobble.
You can count on us!

631
00:40:50.120 --> 00:40:52.640
Okay.
Let's give this a try.

632
00:40:54.120 --> 00:40:55.360
(ALL GRUNTING)

633
00:40:55.680 --> 00:40:56.840
(RUMBLING SOUND)

634
00:40:56.880 --> 00:40:58.880
Do you feel that?
She's starting
to break free.

635
00:40:58.960 --> 00:41:00.560
I don't think so.

636
00:41:05.080 --> 00:41:06.520
Come on, hurry!

637
00:41:06.560 --> 00:41:07.920
Pull! Pull!

638
00:41:09.960 --> 00:41:11.040
Pull!

639
00:41:18.200 --> 00:41:19.320
ROSETTA: Pull!

640
00:41:23.760 --> 00:41:24.880
(SCREAMING)

641
00:41:26.000 --> 00:41:27.200
(GASPING)

642
00:41:33.200 --> 00:41:36.360
Hello?
Is somebody out there?

643
00:41:38.640 --> 00:41:39.840
Anyone?

644
00:41:43.720 --> 00:41:45.560
Grab this! Hurry!

645
00:41:45.600 --> 00:41:46.720
Are you kidding me?

646
00:41:47.040 --> 00:41:49.080
Trust me.
And hold on tight.

647
00:41:51.200 --> 00:41:52.480
Oh, well.

648
00:41:53.640 --> 00:41:54.880
(ALL SCREAMING)

649
00:41:57.440 --> 00:41:58.760
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

650
00:42:02.680 --> 00:42:03.760
(CAR DRIVES AWAY)

651
00:42:05.160 --> 00:42:06.200
We got the...

652
00:42:06.240 --> 00:42:07.520
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

653
00:42:07.560 --> 00:42:09.760
...rescue device.

654
00:42:09.840 --> 00:42:11.760
You scared
the petals right
off of me!

655
00:42:13.240 --> 00:42:15.080
Did we miss anything?

656
00:42:16.400 --> 00:42:21.000
LIZZY: "My,
what a splendid tea service.
I am really quite impressed."

657
00:42:21.520 --> 00:42:23.000
Then I say,

658
00:42:23.080 --> 00:42:26.080
(YAWNING) "Why, thank you,
Tinker Bell.

659
00:42:27.040 --> 00:42:28.760
"You are too kind."

660
00:42:29.760 --> 00:42:32.800
You hold your
pinkie out, like this,

661
00:42:34.080 --> 00:42:40.600
and that's
the way you throw
a proper tea party.

662
00:42:43.120 --> 00:42:44.240
(LAUGHING)

663
00:42:48.120 --> 00:42:49.760
Good night, Lizzy.

664
00:42:53.480 --> 00:42:55.120
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

665
00:43:01.240 --> 00:43:02.280
(SIGHING)

666
00:43:02.320 --> 00:43:03.720
There we... Oh!

667
00:43:05.440 --> 00:43:07.120
I'm going to bed.

668
00:43:15.800 --> 00:43:16.800
(GROANS)

669
00:43:16.840 --> 00:43:19.640
There just aren't
enough hours in the day.

670
00:44:09.240 --> 00:44:10.560
(DRIPPING CONTINUES)

671
00:45:43.120 --> 00:45:44.200
(GRUNTS)

672
00:45:46.080 --> 00:45:48.440
Oh. Good morning,
Tinker Bell.

673
00:45:48.480 --> 00:45:50.160
How did you sleep
last night?

674
00:45:50.200 --> 00:45:54.120
Well, I...
Actually, I didn't,
but that doesn't matter.

675
00:45:54.160 --> 00:45:55.920
You should go downstairs
to your father.

676
00:45:56.000 --> 00:45:57.120
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

677
00:45:57.520 --> 00:45:58.520
Lizzy?

678
00:45:58.600 --> 00:45:59.600
Yes, Father?

679
00:45:59.920 --> 00:46:03.600
Good morning, my dear.
All the leaks seem
to have stopped.

680
00:46:04.000 --> 00:46:06.600
I just wanted to make sure
everything is okay in here.

681
00:46:08.000 --> 00:46:12.120
Yes. Just fine.
No leaks at all. So...

682
00:46:12.680 --> 00:46:15.520
Strange. It's as if they
mended themselves.

683
00:46:17.520 --> 00:46:19.360
It's still raining outside.

684
00:46:19.440 --> 00:46:22.400
I can't imagine how on Earth
such a thing could occur.

685
00:46:24.560 --> 00:46:26.440
Well, there must be
an explanation

686
00:46:26.520 --> 00:46:27.880
that I'm just
not thinking of.

687
00:46:27.960 --> 00:46:30.360
Well, I'm sure you'll
think of it, Father.

688
00:46:30.440 --> 00:46:32.080
Off we go.
Perhaps down
in your study.

689
00:46:32.160 --> 00:46:34.720
You always do your
best thinking there.
I wish you luck.

690
00:46:34.800 --> 00:46:36.720
Okay, well, play nicely.

691
00:46:36.800 --> 00:46:38.680
Yes, of course.
Bye, Father.

692
00:46:41.120 --> 00:46:42.880
(SIGHS) Oh!
That was close.

693
00:46:43.040 --> 00:46:45.720
What are you doing?
This is your chance.

694
00:46:51.880 --> 00:46:54.680
Is that why you
fixed those leaks?

695
00:46:56.720 --> 00:46:59.080
So he can spend
more time with me?

696
00:47:01.360 --> 00:47:04.160
I've really been wanting
to show him this.

697
00:47:05.760 --> 00:47:07.760
Okay, okay. I'll go.

698
00:47:13.640 --> 00:47:15.760
Father,
since you have more time,

699
00:47:15.800 --> 00:47:18.120
maybe I can show you
my scientific research.

700
00:47:18.200 --> 00:47:19.920
DR. GRIFFITHS:
The butterfly. It's gone!

701
00:47:20.000 --> 00:47:21.040
LIZZY: What?

702
00:47:21.280 --> 00:47:24.080
The <i>apatura iris</i>
with the irregular
wing pattern.

703
00:47:24.160 --> 00:47:26.440
I was going to present it
to the museum tonight.

704
00:47:26.520 --> 00:47:30.080
Oh! This was
my big opportunity,
and now it's gone.

705
00:47:31.120 --> 00:47:33.760
Elizabeth,
did you release it?

706
00:47:33.800 --> 00:47:34.840
No.

707
00:47:36.200 --> 00:47:38.000
Well, I didn't do it.

708
00:47:38.560 --> 00:47:40.440
And since there
is no one else
in the house,

709
00:47:40.480 --> 00:47:43.120
there is only one
logical explanation.

710
00:47:44.600 --> 00:47:46.160
It must have been you.

711
00:47:46.240 --> 00:47:47.760
I didn't do it, Father.

712
00:47:48.200 --> 00:47:52.360
I'm going to give
you one more chance.
Tell me the truth.

713
00:47:52.880 --> 00:47:53.960
(SNIFFLES)

714
00:47:54.000 --> 00:47:58.920
I could tell you, Father,
but you wouldn't believe me.

715
00:48:02.120 --> 00:48:07.960
Very well.
Off to your room, young lady.
I'm very disappointed in you.

716
00:48:13.680 --> 00:48:16.840
You know,
I was just thinking,
if Tink were here,

717
00:48:17.320 --> 00:48:19.120
how not quiet it
would be right now.

718
00:48:19.160 --> 00:48:20.240
You can say that again.

719
00:48:20.320 --> 00:48:21.320
(LAUGHING)

720
00:48:21.360 --> 00:48:23.920
Okay, okay, okay.
Who am I?

721
00:48:24.240 --> 00:48:25.360
(INHALES DEEPLY)

722
00:48:26.160 --> 00:48:27.360
(GRUNTING)

723
00:48:28.040 --> 00:48:29.160
(ALL LAUGHING)

724
00:48:29.840 --> 00:48:31.680
That's the exact shade!

725
00:48:33.520 --> 00:48:36.200
BOBBLE: Quite a bit of spirit
in that little tinker, eh?

726
00:48:36.280 --> 00:48:40.400
That's for sure.
In fact, I still can't
believe she got captured.

727
00:48:40.520 --> 00:48:43.840
Yeah. It's very unlike Tink
to be caught
with her guard down.

728
00:48:43.920 --> 00:48:45.560
I wonder what
really happened.

729
00:48:45.640 --> 00:48:47.200
Well, we'll find out soon.

730
00:48:47.280 --> 00:48:49.640
Yep. With every
step we take we come

731
00:48:49.680 --> 00:48:51.760
closer and closer
to Tinker Bell.

732
00:48:52.080 --> 00:48:54.080
She'll tell us
what happened.

733
00:48:54.200 --> 00:48:55.840
(CLEARS THROAT)
Listen,

734
00:48:55.920 --> 00:48:57.600
there's something
you all should know.

735
00:48:59.840 --> 00:49:01.720
Tinker Bell getting trapped
is all my fault!

736
00:49:02.040 --> 00:49:03.160
(ALL GASP)

737
00:49:03.200 --> 00:49:06.200
I slammed that
door on Tinker Bell,
to teach her a lesson.

738
00:49:06.280 --> 00:49:08.680
I tried to get her out,
but the door was stuck.

739
00:49:08.800 --> 00:49:10.960
I tried,
but I couldn't,

740
00:49:11.040 --> 00:49:14.200
and now I've put her
and all of us in danger.

741
00:49:15.720 --> 00:49:17.760
I am so sorry.

742
00:49:21.680 --> 00:49:23.800
Honey,
this is not your fault.

743
00:49:23.880 --> 00:49:27.120
We all know that Tink
can get into plenty of
trouble all by herself.

744
00:49:27.200 --> 00:49:28.840
It scares me to think
what would have happened

745
00:49:28.880 --> 00:49:31.360
if you weren't
there, Vidia.

746
00:49:31.400 --> 00:49:33.360
I don't know what to say.

747
00:49:33.400 --> 00:49:35.960
How about faith...

748
00:49:36.040 --> 00:49:37.120
Trust...

749
00:49:37.440 --> 00:49:38.800
And...
And...

750
00:49:38.880 --> 00:49:40.880
And pixie dust.

751
00:49:41.040 --> 00:49:43.040
ALL: And pixie dust!

752
00:49:43.080 --> 00:49:44.520
BOBBLE: Can you
reach it, Clanky?

753
00:49:44.560 --> 00:49:45.720
(CLANK GRUNTING)

754
00:49:45.760 --> 00:49:47.400
Almost.
Just a little more.

755
00:49:47.480 --> 00:49:48.600
Here, let me.

756
00:49:49.440 --> 00:49:51.760
Okay. Now,
can you see anything?

757
00:49:52.080 --> 00:49:55.280
No! There's a big
building in the way.

758
00:49:55.880 --> 00:49:59.040
BOBBLE: Building.
It's a house.

759
00:49:59.080 --> 00:50:00.960
That's it!
Clanky! We've got it!

760
00:50:01.040 --> 00:50:02.160
CLANK: What've we got?

761
00:50:02.240 --> 00:50:03.280
BOBBLE: House! Get off.

762
00:50:03.360 --> 00:50:04.360
CLANK: I'm sorry.

763
00:50:04.400 --> 00:50:05.600
BOBBLE: I can't feel my legs.

764
00:50:10.360 --> 00:50:15.600
LIZZY:
It doesn't matter what I say.
He never believes me.

765
00:50:17.560 --> 00:50:19.320
I'm so sorry, Lizzy.

766
00:50:22.600 --> 00:50:24.600
I'm so glad you're here.

767
00:50:25.840 --> 00:50:27.720
You're my best friend.

768
00:50:34.000 --> 00:50:35.120
(SIGHING)

769
00:50:35.280 --> 00:50:38.360
I wish I were a fairy,
just like you.

770
00:50:40.040 --> 00:50:43.120
Then I could help
the flowers bloom
and talk to animals

771
00:50:43.200 --> 00:50:46.480
and fly around
with the other fairies
all the time.

772
00:50:51.720 --> 00:50:53.400
That would be fun.

773
00:51:05.280 --> 00:51:07.000
Where are we going?

774
00:51:35.640 --> 00:51:36.760
(GASPING)

775
00:52:02.760 --> 00:52:03.880
(LAUGHING)

776
00:52:03.920 --> 00:52:05.040
Oh!

777
00:52:05.120 --> 00:52:06.320
(CRASHING)

778
00:52:06.480 --> 00:52:07.600
(GASPING)

779
00:52:07.720 --> 00:52:08.840
(LAUGHING)

780
00:52:08.880 --> 00:52:09.920
(CRASHING)

781
00:52:10.000 --> 00:52:11.880
What is going on up there?

782
00:52:21.720 --> 00:52:22.840
Whoa!

783
00:52:25.040 --> 00:52:26.280
(CRASHING)

784
00:52:27.040 --> 00:52:29.520
I was going to present it
to the museum tonight.

785
00:52:29.560 --> 00:52:31.400
Now the butterfly is gone.

786
00:52:32.360 --> 00:52:33.480
Whoa!

787
00:52:43.080 --> 00:52:44.160
Whoa!

788
00:52:45.920 --> 00:52:47.160
(LIZZY LAUGHING)

789
00:52:54.080 --> 00:52:59.080
Oh, my! I'm...
I'm flying!

790
00:53:00.920 --> 00:53:02.240
Whoa!

791
00:53:02.920 --> 00:53:06.920
Look at me!
Whee! I'm a fairy!

792
00:53:12.120 --> 00:53:13.560
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

793
00:53:17.440 --> 00:53:18.800
All clear!

794
00:53:20.400 --> 00:53:21.680
(CLANK GRUNTING)

795
00:53:24.440 --> 00:53:25.840
IRIDESSA: Sorry.
Oh! Careful.

796
00:53:25.920 --> 00:53:27.120
That's my ear.
SILVERMIST: Sorry.

797
00:53:27.200 --> 00:53:28.600
FAWN: Sorry.
That's the nose. Careful.

798
00:53:28.640 --> 00:53:30.320
ROSETTA: Whoops! Sorry.
Can't see!

799
00:53:30.600 --> 00:53:32.400
Okay.
Tinker Bell is upstairs.

800
00:53:32.520 --> 00:53:34.280
The little girl
has her in a cage.

801
00:53:34.320 --> 00:53:35.960
(GASPS) In a cage?

802
00:53:36.000 --> 00:53:37.920
And there's
also a large human
in the house

803
00:53:38.000 --> 00:53:40.000
who doesn't like
creatures with wings.

804
00:53:40.080 --> 00:53:42.600
He pins them up
in display cases.

805
00:53:43.360 --> 00:53:45.800
Great. Anything else?

806
00:53:45.840 --> 00:53:47.040
Oh, yes. The cat.

807
00:53:47.280 --> 00:53:48.920
Cat! What cat?

808
00:53:49.520 --> 00:53:51.280
That cat!
That cat!

809
00:53:53.320 --> 00:53:54.400
(SNARLING)

810
00:53:55.400 --> 00:53:59.120
Fawn, you're an animal fairy.
What are we supposed to do?

811
00:54:01.040 --> 00:54:02.040
BOBBLE: Fawn?

812
00:54:02.120 --> 00:54:03.120
Fly!

813
00:54:03.200 --> 00:54:04.200
ROSETTA:
Our wings are wet.

814
00:54:04.280 --> 00:54:05.600
BOBBLE:
And who knows
when they'll be dry.

815
00:54:05.720 --> 00:54:07.520
Okay, okay. Run!

816
00:54:07.880 --> 00:54:09.120
(SNARLING)

817
00:54:09.880 --> 00:54:10.920
(HISSING)

818
00:54:20.240 --> 00:54:22.360
Clank!
Come on!

819
00:54:22.400 --> 00:54:23.560
Whoa!

820
00:54:24.520 --> 00:54:25.840
(CLANK SCREAMING)

821
00:54:26.720 --> 00:54:28.280
BOBBLE: Clank!

822
00:54:28.360 --> 00:54:30.080
I'm okay.

823
00:54:31.840 --> 00:54:34.720
We still need to
get to that stairwell.
Any ideas?

824
00:54:34.800 --> 00:54:36.800
If we could
just build a bridge
or something.

825
00:54:36.880 --> 00:54:38.160
That's it.
A bridge!

826
00:54:38.240 --> 00:54:39.760
CLANK: Guys? Guys?

827
00:54:39.960 --> 00:54:41.160
A bridge made
out of what?

828
00:54:41.240 --> 00:54:42.360
CLANK: Guys!

829
00:54:44.240 --> 00:54:46.240
Clank!
You're a genius!

830
00:54:46.640 --> 00:54:48.200
Huh? Uh.

831
00:54:48.240 --> 00:54:49.480
(LAUGHING)

832
00:54:50.360 --> 00:54:51.680
It was nothing.

833
00:54:54.720 --> 00:54:56.920
All right.
Let's do this.

834
00:55:06.600 --> 00:55:08.600
We need
some more plates!

835
00:55:08.640 --> 00:55:11.000
Okay.
Start passing
them up, Clanky.

836
00:55:11.440 --> 00:55:14.880
Aye, aye!
Here they come!

837
00:55:18.000 --> 00:55:20.760
Get ready for more.
Oh, hello!

838
00:55:21.120 --> 00:55:22.280
(SCREAMING)

839
00:55:22.800 --> 00:55:24.840
We've got a full
plate back here!

840
00:55:24.960 --> 00:55:28.640
No, no, no.
No. No, please.

841
00:55:29.080 --> 00:55:30.080
BOBBLE: Get back!

842
00:55:32.160 --> 00:55:33.240
(ALL SCREAMING)

843
00:55:41.040 --> 00:55:42.320
(CLATTERING)

844
00:55:44.800 --> 00:55:45.920
BOBBLE: Get back!

845
00:55:45.960 --> 00:55:49.080
Rosetta!
Is this what
I think it is?

846
00:55:49.560 --> 00:55:52.760
That is exactly
what you think it is.
Catnip!

847
00:55:53.400 --> 00:55:55.920
You get to Tink
and we'll take
care of the cat!

848
00:55:56.000 --> 00:55:56.960
Got it!

849
00:56:05.240 --> 00:56:06.320
LIZZY: Whoa!

850
00:56:06.400 --> 00:56:07.640
(CRASHING)

851
00:56:15.160 --> 00:56:17.200
DR. GRIFFITHS: Lizzy?
LIZZY: Coming, Father!

852
00:56:17.600 --> 00:56:18.840
Lizzy?

853
00:56:18.880 --> 00:56:21.440
Why, hello, Father.
May I help you?

854
00:56:21.640 --> 00:56:22.720
What's going on in here?

855
00:56:22.800 --> 00:56:23.840
Nothing.

856
00:56:23.920 --> 00:56:26.520
Nothing? Sounds like
a herd of elephants

857
00:56:26.560 --> 00:56:28.080
have been
marching up here.

858
00:56:30.040 --> 00:56:33.600
Look at this room.
It looks like
a cyclone hit it.

859
00:56:34.360 --> 00:56:35.680
It's not that bad.

860
00:56:35.760 --> 00:56:37.080
Not that bad?

861
00:56:37.840 --> 00:56:40.560
Your books are
all over the floor,
your toys are everywhere

862
00:56:40.640 --> 00:56:43.320
and you tore
your curtains. What?

863
00:56:44.320 --> 00:56:47.200
How did you get footprints
on the ceiling?

864
00:56:47.760 --> 00:56:49.360
This is simply too much.

865
00:56:49.440 --> 00:56:52.560
A temper tantrum
of this magnitude
is unacceptable.

866
00:56:52.640 --> 00:56:54.400
But I wasn't
having a tantrum!

867
00:56:54.480 --> 00:56:57.720
Then how did this happen?
And the truth this time.

868
00:56:58.360 --> 00:57:02.680
If I tell you the truth,
you still won't believe me.

869
00:57:03.200 --> 00:57:04.960
Elizabeth, the truth.

870
00:57:06.480 --> 00:57:09.640
I was flying.
My fairy showed me how.

871
00:57:09.720 --> 00:57:14.160
Oh, for goodness sake.
Your make-believe fairy
did this?

872
00:57:14.240 --> 00:57:16.480
You've got to stop
this nonsense!

873
00:57:16.560 --> 00:57:19.120
But it's
not nonsense, Father.
It's the truth!

874
00:57:19.200 --> 00:57:21.280
You have a real fairy
living in your room?

875
00:57:21.360 --> 00:57:23.320
Yes! And I can prove it.

876
00:57:26.480 --> 00:57:28.920
Just look at
the research we did.

877
00:57:33.440 --> 00:57:36.320
Elizabeth. This is what
you've been doing?

878
00:57:37.280 --> 00:57:40.720
Field journals are to
be filled with fact,
not fairy tales.

879
00:57:40.760 --> 00:57:42.920
But Father,
these are facts!

880
00:57:43.320 --> 00:57:47.080
I don't understand
this foolishness, Lizzy.
You have such talent.

881
00:57:47.120 --> 00:57:48.880
Why would you
waste it this way?

882
00:57:48.920 --> 00:57:52.280
Why can't
you just believe me?

883
00:57:52.360 --> 00:57:54.240
I believe in
what is real,

884
00:57:54.280 --> 00:57:57.320
and it's about time
you started doing the same.

885
00:57:57.400 --> 00:57:58.840
Father, wait!

886
00:57:59.280 --> 00:58:02.080
I know this is
difficult for you
to understand,

887
00:58:02.120 --> 00:58:04.760
but this is all
make-believe.

888
00:58:04.800 --> 00:58:06.280
No! They're real!

889
00:58:06.320 --> 00:58:08.120
Elizabeth,
this discussion is over.

890
00:58:09.640 --> 00:58:11.040
But Father!

891
00:58:11.960 --> 00:58:13.080
(GRUNTS)

892
00:58:13.800 --> 00:58:15.000
(BELL JINGLING)

893
00:58:20.160 --> 00:58:23.000
It... It...

894
00:58:24.120 --> 00:58:27.680
See? I told you.
Fairies are real!

895
00:58:29.680 --> 00:58:30.880
(WHIMPERS)

896
00:58:32.040 --> 00:58:34.840
It's okay.
She won't hurt you.

897
00:58:37.400 --> 00:58:40.600
It's...
Well, it's extraordinary!

898
00:58:40.840 --> 00:58:42.960
LIZZY: Aren't her
wings beautiful?

899
00:58:43.040 --> 00:58:47.160
Yes. Very similar to <i>Apoidea.</i>
Or, no, no, <i>odonata.</i>

900
00:58:47.600 --> 00:58:51.080
Look at
the limb proportionality
to the cranial radius.

901
00:58:51.280 --> 00:58:52.320
Fascinating!

902
00:58:52.360 --> 00:58:53.600
Isn't she magical?

903
00:58:54.120 --> 00:58:57.160
She's some sort of
evolutionary mutation.

904
00:58:57.320 --> 00:58:59.600
She's not a bug,
she's a person.

905
00:58:59.680 --> 00:59:01.000
DR. GRIFFITHS: Exactly!
Tinker Bell!

906
00:59:01.040 --> 00:59:03.040
DR. GRIFFITHS:
This is going to be
the discovery of the century!

907
00:59:03.120 --> 00:59:04.240
Tink, watch out!

908
00:59:04.320 --> 00:59:05.320
Vidia?

909
00:59:05.440 --> 00:59:06.400
Get out of the way!

910
00:59:07.680 --> 00:59:09.000
(TINKER BELL GRUNTS)

911
00:59:09.520 --> 00:59:12.200
I must get this
to the museum
right away!

912
00:59:12.320 --> 00:59:13.680
Father, no!

913
00:59:14.400 --> 00:59:16.480
Please, Father! Wait!

914
00:59:19.440 --> 00:59:20.840
You can't do this!

915
00:59:21.000 --> 00:59:22.440
Lizzy, I don't
have much time.

916
00:59:22.880 --> 00:59:25.360
The trustees will
only wait for me
until 9:00.

917
00:59:25.440 --> 00:59:27.360
Please,
go back in the house.

918
00:59:27.440 --> 00:59:30.640
Don't worry.
Mrs. Perkins will
be here any second.

919
00:59:36.040 --> 00:59:38.520
Tinker Bell,
I'm so sorry!

920
00:59:39.040 --> 00:59:41.880
My father's
taking your friend
to the city!

921
00:59:41.920 --> 00:59:43.720
(MR. TWITCHES MEOWING)

922
00:59:43.800 --> 00:59:45.200
ALL: Step, step, step.

923
00:59:45.280 --> 00:59:46.480
(CLANK LAUGHING)

924
00:59:47.040 --> 00:59:48.560
Tinker Bell?
Tinker Bell!

925
00:59:48.880 --> 00:59:50.720
Look, it's your friends.

926
00:59:51.640 --> 00:59:53.440
Hurry.

927
00:59:53.520 --> 00:59:55.520
That's it.
Good kitty.

928
01:00:00.160 --> 01:00:02.080
Look, Lizzy's father
trapped Vidia
in a jar

929
01:00:02.080 --> 01:00:03.360
while she was saving me.

930
01:00:03.400 --> 01:00:04.880
We have to hurry
and rescue her.

931
01:00:04.960 --> 01:00:06.240
Here we go again!

932
01:00:06.320 --> 01:00:07.480
How are we
gonna get there?

933
01:00:07.560 --> 01:00:09.080
Yeah,
it's still raining.

934
01:00:09.120 --> 01:00:11.440
Maybe we can't
fly in the rain,

935
01:00:11.520 --> 01:00:13.560
but I think I know
someone who can.

936
01:00:24.760 --> 01:00:26.600
I'm scared, Tinker Bell.

937
01:00:26.640 --> 01:00:29.000
Floating around my room
is one thing,

938
01:00:29.080 --> 01:00:31.080
but flying all
the way to London...

939
01:00:34.880 --> 01:00:35.880
That easy, huh?

940
01:00:37.760 --> 01:00:39.560
Okay. I'll be brave.

941
01:00:41.120 --> 01:00:44.080
All right, fairies.
We need all the pixie dust
we can get.

942
01:00:44.160 --> 01:00:47.080
This girl's got
a long journey
ahead of her.

943
01:00:58.120 --> 01:00:59.480
All aboard!

944
01:01:02.480 --> 01:01:03.680
Ready?

945
01:01:04.080 --> 01:01:05.120
Whoa!

946
01:01:05.160 --> 01:01:06.800
This better work.

947
01:01:08.600 --> 01:01:09.680
(CRASHING)

948
01:01:09.800 --> 01:01:11.960
LIZZY: Oh!
Sorry, fairies.

949
01:01:12.640 --> 01:01:14.200
Whoa! Oh!

950
01:01:15.400 --> 01:01:16.600
Whoa!

951
01:01:20.120 --> 01:01:21.560
ALL: Whoa!

952
01:01:21.680 --> 01:01:22.800
Careful now!

953
01:01:25.120 --> 01:01:28.000
Hi, Mrs. Perkins.
Bye, Mrs. Perkins.

954
01:01:28.160 --> 01:01:30.960
Bye, dear.
Fly back soon.

955
01:01:31.040 --> 01:01:32.160
(CHUCKLING)

956
01:01:32.320 --> 01:01:33.480
(GASPING)

957
01:01:34.800 --> 01:01:36.160
(CAR ENGINE RATTLING)

958
01:01:54.000 --> 01:01:55.160
Whoa!

959
01:02:00.240 --> 01:02:01.880
Oh! Good idea.

960
01:02:13.640 --> 01:02:14.680
Oh!

961
01:02:27.520 --> 01:02:28.640
Whoa!

962
01:02:43.640 --> 01:02:44.680
(TIRES SCREECHING)

963
01:02:44.720 --> 01:02:45.880
Sorry!

964
01:02:46.920 --> 01:02:48.240
Out of the way!

965
01:02:48.280 --> 01:02:49.360
(HONKING)

966
01:02:52.360 --> 01:02:53.360
There he is!

967
01:02:58.320 --> 01:03:01.840
Tinker Bell,
I can't keep up.
He's going too fast.

968
01:03:12.080 --> 01:03:13.560
(MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

969
01:03:17.160 --> 01:03:20.320
Tink! Tinker Bell, no!

970
01:03:47.880 --> 01:03:49.040
(ELECTRICITY BUZZING)

971
01:04:07.560 --> 01:04:08.640
(TIRES SCREECHING)

972
01:04:17.720 --> 01:04:18.800
(ENGINE STALLING)

973
01:04:19.760 --> 01:04:23.040
No, no, no, no, no, no!
Come on!

974
01:04:25.520 --> 01:04:26.560
(HONKING)

975
01:04:26.640 --> 01:04:28.040
Come on, please,
let them still be there.

976
01:04:35.640 --> 01:04:37.520
LIZZY: Father!

977
01:04:37.560 --> 01:04:38.880
What in the world?

978
01:04:39.280 --> 01:04:40.480
Father, stop!

979
01:04:40.560 --> 01:04:41.720
(GASPING)

980
01:04:41.760 --> 01:04:42.960
Don't take her in there!

981
01:04:45.280 --> 01:04:48.800
It... It... It...
It can't be.

982
01:04:53.400 --> 01:04:56.680
Lizzy? You're flying.

983
01:04:58.160 --> 01:04:59.560
Yes, I am.

984
01:05:01.840 --> 01:05:05.040
But how?
How are you doing that?

985
01:05:08.160 --> 01:05:10.160
My friends showed me how.

986
01:05:16.240 --> 01:05:18.760
I... I don't understand.

987
01:05:19.400 --> 01:05:21.600
You don't have
to understand.

988
01:05:22.880 --> 01:05:25.240
You just
have to believe.

989
01:05:30.160 --> 01:05:31.760
I do believe.

990
01:05:33.120 --> 01:05:34.600
I do believe!

991
01:05:35.600 --> 01:05:37.280
Oh! Father!

992
01:05:39.800 --> 01:05:42.280
Lizzy, I'm so sorry,
I'm so sorry.

993
01:05:43.480 --> 01:05:46.800
I'll never doubt you again.

994
01:06:01.200 --> 01:06:02.360
TINKER BELL: Vidia!

995
01:06:02.880 --> 01:06:04.640
